crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: APP-DETECT Apple Messages push.apple.com DNS TXT request attempt

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a credential harvester and data exfiltration tool. It displays a fake installer alert dialog to phish for the user's password. It then uses the Dropbox API to exfiltrate data, as indicated by network requests to `content.dropboxapi.com/2/files/upload`. Additionally, it performs reconnaissance by fetching the external IP address from `api.ipify.org` and uses `NSTask` to launch a dropped application (`/var/tmp/versus.app`) and a decoy URL (`zoom.versusx.us`).
